feat(robust-quant): Robust Quant Phase — anti-overfitting infrastructure

Eight invariants. None of them generate signals. All of them gate them.

Priority 1 — Backfill infrastructure
- scripts/top100_backfill.py: 5-year curated TOP100 yfinance pull, idempotent
  (>= 1000 bars / symbol), concurrent with semaphore, structured report
- scripts/rolling_update.py: daily incremental bars from last persisted date
- scripts/data_integrity_checker.py: missing-bars / duplicates / anomalous
  prices (|return| > 50%) / OHLC sanity / thin coverage; exit 1 on failure

Priority 2 — Regime Stress Test Engine
- strategy/stress/regime_segments.py: 6 known segments (2020 crash,
  2020 recovery, 2021 euphoria, 2022 bear, 2023 AI break, 2024 megacap)
  + auto-detector for sideways/euphoria/low-vol windows in any series
- strategy/stress/stress_runner.py: per-segment metrics + composites
  (cross_regime_consistency, cross_regime_min_pf, single_period_dominance)

Priority 3 — Strategy Correlation Engine
- strategy/correlation/correlation_analyzer.py: pairwise Pearson on daily
  realized-R + drawdown overlap + signal overlap (Jaccard). Flags pairs
  where any metric exceeds threshold (0.75 / 0.6 / 0.5).

Priority 4 — Robustness Validator
- app/strategy_lab/robustness.py: gates cross_regime_consistency (>=60%),
  single_period_dominance (<=60%), MC p05 ratio (>=1.0),
  MC profitable (>=60%). Composite robustness_score 0..1.

Priority 5 — Risk Allocation Engine
- app/risk_engine/allocator.py: per-regime modifier
  (trending_up=1.0, sideways=0.4, bearish=0.3, …). Disabled => weight 0,
  WATCH => weight halved. Outputs weight + max_exposure + signal_risk_pct
  with portfolio-level concurrency cap.

Priority 6 — Portfolio Backtester
- app/portfolio_backtester/simulator.py: multi-strategy concurrent runner
  with max_concurrent_positions cap, 1% risk per trade, max-hold timeout.
  Returns portfolio sharpe/DD, equity curve, per-strategy breakdown,
  exposure heat-map.

Priority 7 — Edge Persistence
- app/edge/edge_persistence.py: 14-bar rolling expectancy series,
  half-life days (fit y = a*exp(-t/tau)), decay velocity (R/week).
  Half-life = ln(2)*tau when decay slope < 0, else None.

Priority 8 — Research Quality Gates
- app/strategy_registry/research_quality.py:
  production_research_score = 0.20*sample + 0.20*overfit + 0.15*regime
                            + 0.15*correlation + 0.15*decay + 0.15*robust
  >= 0.65 → ACTIVE
  >= 0.40 → RESEARCH_ONLY (visible only in research panels)
  <  0.40 → DISABLED

API endpoints
- /api/v1/stress/run/{strategy}?symbol=…
- /api/v1/stress/segments
- /api/v1/correlation/matrix?window=…
- /api/v1/risk/allocation?regime=…
- /api/v1/portfolio/simulate
- /api/v1/persistence/?window=…
- /api/v1/quality/

Scheduler additions
- 08:00 mon-fri  rolling_update          (incremental OHLCV)
- 02:00 sat      integrity_check
- 22:00 sun      correlation_refresh
- 23:00 sun      universe_rebuild  (already existed; pre-Robust-phase)

Frontend
- /terminal/robustness: research quality verdict table, strategy
  correlation matrix, edge persistence half-life table, risk allocation
- /terminal navigation updated: Brief / Performance / Robustness

Tests: 132/132 passing (15 new)
- test_robust_quant.py: stress segments + filter, correlation flagging,
  robustness gates, allocator regime sensitivity, portfolio max_concurrent,
  persistence rolling expectancy, quality ACTIVE/RESEARCH_ONLY/DISABLED

Iron rules upheld
- No lookahead: stress runs use backtest_engine_v2's next-bar fills
- All data traceable: stress segments are real date ranges, correlation
  is computed from real edge_signals only
- No fake stats: portfolio sim, persistence, quality all derive from
  evaluated outcomes
- Production gates compound: ranker × robustness × research_quality
- Quality + correlation now gate ACTIVE status — fewer, better signals

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
